<BaseLayout title="Ronin Run - Jonathan To">
  <div slot="breadcrumb" class="breadcrumb-bar">
    <a href="/personal-projects/">PersonalProjects()</a>
    <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
    <span class="breadcrumb-current">Ronin_Run</span>
  </div>

  <ProjectHeader
    title="Ronin Run"
    subtitle="Programmer · Designer · Solo"
    tags={[
      { label: "Programming", type: "programming" },
      { label: "Design", type: "design" },
      { label: "Unity", type: "unity" },
    ]}
    description="A 3D movement game built around Source-engine-style movement - air strafing, bunny hopping - extended with a shuriken toolkit that adds distinct traversal abilities. My first Unity project, and an ongoing exercise in turning a tech demo into an actual game."
  />

  <VideoEmbed
    videoId="UVIb1568SVI"
    caption="// fig_01 - Source-style movement + shuriken traversal · Ronin Run"
    alt="Ronin Run Gameplay Demo"
  />

  <div class="grid gap-6" style="grid-template-columns: 1fr 260px;">
    <TextBlock
      title="Overview"
      content="Ronin Run started as a movement system - a personal project to learn Unity by implementing Source-engine-style physics movement in 3D. Over time it grew into a broader design exploration: how do you build a game around movement as the core loop? The shuriken system was the answer - a modular set of throwable abilities, each one a different traversal verb, designed to expand the space the player can reach and how they get there."
    />

    <TextBlock
      title="Contributions"
      content={[
        "Programmed Source-style movement system (air strafing, bunny hopping) from scratch in Unity",
        "Designed and programmed the full shuriken toolkit - platform, teleport, slingshot, grapple, and explosion variants",
        "Authored the GDD: defined gameplay goals, documented the design process, and scoped the project from tech demo to game",
      ]}
    />

    <div style="grid-column:2; grid-row:1/3;">
      <ProjectDetails
        meta={[
          { key: "status", value: "WIP", highlight: true },
          { key: "year", value: "2022–present" },
          { key: "duration", value: "4 months / ongoing" },
          { key: "team_size", value: "1 (solo)" },
          { key: "platform", value: "PC" },
          { key: "context", value: "Tech demo · Self-learning" },
        ]}
        links={[
          {
            label: "View on GitHub",
            href: "https://github.com/JonTo212/RoninRun",
            icon: "◇",
          },
        ]}
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:1rem;">
    <div style="border:1px solid var(--border); background:var(--bg-panel);">
      <div
        style="padding:10px 16px; background:var(--bg-card); border-bottom:1px solid var(--border); font-family:'Commit Mono',monospace; font-size:1.1rem; color:var(--green-dim);"
      >
        // Key Features
      </div>
    </div>

    <KeyFeature
      index={1}
      title="Source-Style Movement"
      description="3D movement system modelled after Source-engine physics - air strafing, bunny hopping, and momentum preservation. Wish-direction input is projected against the current velocity to allow mid-air direction control without breaking speed, replicating the feel of classic movement shooters. I then layered abilities from popular FPS games to round out the base movement toolkit, including wall-running, sliding, ledge grab with mantling, a dash and a double jump."
      snippetLabel="PlayerControllerV2.cs - AirMove / AirControl / Accelerate"
      videoSrc="/videos/source-movement-demo.mp4"
      snippetFilename="PlayerControllerV2.cs"
      snippetCode={airStrafeSnippetPlain}
      flip={true}
    >
      <pre
        slot="snippet-code"
        style="margin:0; padding:1.25rem 1.5rem; overflow-x:auto; background:var(--bg); font-size:12px; line-height:1.8; white-space:pre-wrap; word-break:break-word;"><code class="font-mono text-(--text-code)" set:html={airStrafeSnippetHtml} /></pre>
    </KeyFeature>

    <KeyFeature
      index={2}
      title="Shuriken Toolkit"
      description="A set of throwable abilities, each one a distinct traversal mechanic: a platform shuriken that spawns a jumpable surface mid-air, a teleport shuriken that snaps the player to impact point, slingshot and grapple shurikens for momentum-based traversal, and an explosion shuriken that functions as a blast jump. Each variant shares a common projectile base with a pluggable on-land behaviour."
      snippetLabel="ShurikenBaseClass.cs / WallRunShuriken.cs - AttachToSurface"
      videoSrc="/videos/shurikens-demo.mp4"
      snippetFilename="ShurikenBaseClass.cs"
      snippetCode={shurikenSnippetPlain}
    >
      <pre
        slot="snippet-code"
        style="margin:0; padding:1.25rem 1.5rem; overflow-x:auto; background:var(--bg); font-size:12px; line-height:1.8; white-space:pre-wrap; word-break:break-word;"><code class="font-mono text-(--text-code)" set:html={shurikenSnippetHtml} /></pre>
    </KeyFeature>
  </div>

  <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:2rem;">
    <DeepDiveBlock
      title="Deep dive - from movement system to game"
      steps={[
        {
          tag: "problem",
          icon: "◎",
          title: "A tech demo with no destination",
          body: "Ronin Run started as exactly that - a movement system and nothing more. The mechanics worked, but there was no direction: no defined goals, no player purpose, no reason to engage beyond the feel of the movement itself. Getting from A to B isn't a game.",
        },
        {
          tag: "approach",
          icon: "◈",
          title: "Back to basics - defining the game through documentation",
          body: "The answer was to step away from the engine and go back to fundamentals: writing a GDD, defining a theme, articulating what the gameplay should feel like and why. Ideation and documentation forced hard questions about purpose - what are the shurikens for, what does the player want to reach, what makes movement meaningful in this context.",
        },
        {
          tag: "result",
          icon: "▸",
          title: "Still a WIP - but one with a direction",
          body: "The project is ongoing, but it's no longer just a tech demo. The shurikens have defined roles, the movement has a context to exist in, and there's a design document anchoring decisions. The work left is refinement: the shurikens need to serve exploration and traversal more clearly before the game can be called done.",
        },
      ]}
      slider={{
        label: "ronin_run_design_visual",
        beforeSrc: "",
        afterSrc: "",
      }}
    />

    <TextBlock
      title="Takeaways"
      content={[
        {
          heading: "Simple is good",
          body: "More mechanics don't make a better game. The movement system worked on its own - adding the shuriken toolkit without a clear design goal for each one led to scope creep that the project is still recovering from.",
        },
        {
          heading: "Document before you build",
          body: "Jumping straight into implementation is fast until it isn't. Writing the GDD - defining gameplay goals, player purpose, and mechanic roles - was what finally gave the project a foundation to build on rather than away from.",
        },
